data.name: Chainlink
data.summary: Chainlink announced the Chainlink Reserve has accumulated over 973,700 LINK tokens to support network growth, converting network revenue from off-chain enterprise payments and on-chain service fees. Additionally, November 2025 saw several strategic partnerships, including with UBS for tokenized fund workflows, FTSE Russell for on-chain indices, and central banks for cross-border settlements, alongside the launch of Chainlink Runtime Environment (CRE) and Confidential Compute. SWIFT is also set to officially launch its integration with Chainlink's Cross-Chain Interoperability Protocol (CCIP) in November 2025, connecting blockchain technology to over 11,000 banks and institutions worldwide.
